parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Airbag Sensor Failure (Passenger Occupancy Detection System - PODS)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag sensor can cause the airbag to not deploy in the event of an accident, potentially leading to serious injury or death.
symptoms: Airbag warning light illuminates
passenger airbag may not deploy in the event of an accident
inability to use the front passenger seat.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to the airbag not deploying in the event of an accident, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag warning light comes on
the passenger airbag is switched off
the airbag detection system may be faulty
and the airbag may not deploy when needed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or shut down while driving, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The battery dies
the engine turns off
the vehicle stalls
the electrical system malfunctions
and warning lights come on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake warning light comes on
the brake booster is faulty
the brakes are extremely sensitive
and the vehicle abruptly grinds to a stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause the vehicle to stall or shut down while driving, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The fuel injector MIL code comes on
the vehicle misfires
and the vehicle loses full driving power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the BCM can cause various electrical systems to malfunction, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The doors lock and unlock randomly
the lights stay on even when the doors are closed
and the visor lights do not work consistently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ADAS can cause the vehicle to malfunction, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The blind spot awareness system does not alert to cars on the driver's side
the blind spot light remains on after a turn signal is activated
and the system malfunctions while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake booster can cause the brakes to become spongy or unresponsive, leading to a loss of vehicle control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to stop or slow down
the "Brake Booster Faulty" warning light appears on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Uneven brake wear can cause the brakes to fail prematurely, leading to a loss of vehicle control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake pads wear unevenly
the rotors are warped or gauged
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the automatic braking system can cause the vehicle to stop suddenly or unexpectedly, leading to a loss of vehicle control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle stops suddenly or unexpectedly
the brakes engage without warning
the vehicle slows down or stops without input from the driver
the "Brake Booster Faulty" warning light appears on the dashboard.
